{{About|video game|logical problems involved in the concept of time travel|temporal paradox|the 2008 fantasy novel|Artemis Fowl: The Time Paradox}}
{{Infobox video game |title = Time Paradox |image = Time Paradox.jpg |developer = [[Flair Software]] |publisher = Flair Software |released = 1996 |genre = [[adventure game|Adventure]] |modes = [[Single-player]] |platforms = [[DOS]] }}
'''''Time Paradox''''' (not to be confused with the [[Sharp X1]] title ''Timeparadox'') is a [[point-and-click adventure game]] developed and released by [[Flair Software]] for the PC [[DOS]] in 1996 only in Europe.
==Plot== A futuristic agent named Kay is sent on a mission to stop the evil [[Morgan le Fay|Morgana Le Fay]]. She first travels back in time to "the time of dinosaurs and cavemen" (sic), and then jumps to the medieval era in order to find and rescue the wizard [[Merlin]] from Morgana's castle and eventually defeat the sorceress.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/PCSpiel0995#page/n3/mode/2up/ |title=PC Spiel Magazine (September 1995) |publisher=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref><ref name=pcp/><ref name=aa>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.adventure-archiv.com/t2/paradoxreviewe.htm |title=Time Paradox - Review english |publisher=Adventure-archiv.com |date=2002-10-20 |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref>
==Development== ''Time Paradox'' has been in development for several years, having been in first publicly shown in 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/amiga-world-1993-12/Amiga_World_Vol_09_12_1993_Dec#page/n29/mode/2up/ |title=Amiga World Magazine (December 1993) |publisher=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref> The game was originally supposed to be released as ''Genesis'' already in the first half of 1994 and to be a [[full motion video|FMV based]], featuring digitized graphics. Besides the PC version, the developers also planned to create the [[Amiga]] computer and [[CD32]] versions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://amr.abime.net/review_23477 |title=Genesis preview from CU Amiga (Nov 1993) - Amiga Magazine Rack |publisher=Amr.abime.net |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/Amiga_CD_Format_1993_Future_Publishing_GB_supplement_issue_051#page/n7/mode/2up/ |title=Amiga CD Format (1993)(Future Publishing)(GB)[supplement, issue 051&#93; |publisher=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.przygodoskop.pl/507/encyklopedia.htm |title=Time Paradox - gra przygodowa - przygodówka :: Przygodoskop |publisher=Przygodoskop.pl |date= |language=Polish |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mobygames.com/game/dos/time-paradox/trivia |title=Time Paradox for DOS (1996) Trivia |publisher=MobyGames.com |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref>
==Reception== The game was poorly received by gaming press upon its release,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/secretservicemagazine-1995-12/SecretService_12_1995#page/n9/mode/2up/ |title=Secret Service Magazine (December 1995) |publisher=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref> including receiving one star out of five in Germany's ''PC Player''.<ref name=pcp>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/PC-Player-German-Magazine-1997-06/PC-Player-1997-06#page/n114/mode/1up |title=PC Player German Magazine 1997-06 |publisher=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref> It also got low review scores in Polish magazines ''Gambler'' (48%) and ''Secret Service'' (2/10).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/gambler_magazine-1997-02/Gambler_02_1997#page/n21/mode/2up/ |title=Gambler Magazine (February 1997) |publisher=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/secretservicemagazine-1997-04/SecretService_04_1997#page/n41/mode/2up/ |title=Secret Service Magazine (April 1997) |publisher=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2015-03-28}}</ref> Retrospectively, Adventure-Archiv rated it a 57% in 2002.<ref name=aa/>
==See also== *''[[Chronicles of the Sword]]'', another 1996 adventure game with a similar quest to defeat Morgana (albeit no time travel)
