|[[Black Triangle (UFO)]]
|The "St. Clair Triangle", "UFO Over Illinois", "Southern Illinois UFO", or "Highland, Illinois UFO" sighting occurred on January 5, 2000 over the towns of Highland, Dupo, Lebanon, Summerfield, Millstadt, and O'Fallon, Illinois, beginning shortly after 4:00 am. Five on-duty Illinois police officers in separate locales, along with various other witnesses, sighted and reported a massive, silent, triangular aircraft operating at an unusual range of near-hover to incredible high speed at treetop altitudes. The incident was examined in an [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] Special "Seeing is Believing" by [[Peter Jennings]], an hour-long special "UFOs Over Illinois", produced by [[Discovery Channel]], a [[Sci Fi Channel (United States)|Sci Fi Channel]] special entitled "Proof Positive" as well as a 28-minute independent documentary titled "The Edge of Reality: Illinois UFO, January 5, 2000" by Darryl Barker Productions, St. Louis, Missouri.
