|February 19, 2018
|Desert
|Arizona
|[[2018 Arizona UFO sightings]]
|According to the Federal Aviation Administration, three commercial pilots saw an unidentified object fly over them in open airspace above Arizona. The pilots of a Phoenix Air Learjet 36, an Airbus A321 and American Airlines Flight 1095  radioed-in the sightings minutes from each other. The air traffic controller was unable to verify that any other aircraft in the area at the time, according to the FAA. The odd sightings began around 3:30pm as the Albuquerque Air Traffic Center received reports from several eastbound aircraft that something passed over them at an altitude of 40,000 feet. This incident happened just 500 miles away from historic Roswell, New Mexico.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Fearnow |first1=Benjamin |title=FAA AUDIO: PERPLEXED PILOTS REPORT UFO SIGHTING ABOVE NEW MEXICO, ARIZONA DESERT |url=http://www.newsweek.com/ufo-sighting-new-mexico-arizona-albuquerque-air-traffic-control-american-861975 |website=Tech & Science |publisher=Newsweek |accessdate=4 July 2018}}</ref> Investigator [[Joe Nickell]] researched this sighting and conferred with a former Special Operations pilot [[10036 McGaha|James McGaha]]. They concluded that the shiny object "was relatively stationary" and that a "very bright light source ... during the daytime, it is most likely a reflection of sunlight off an object. After noting the time, and place they concluded that what the pilots saw was mostly likely a "high-altitude research balloon".<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Nickell |first1=Joe|authorlink=Joe Nickell |title=UFO over Arizona Likely an IFO |journal=Skeptical Inquirer |date=2018 |volume=42 |issue=4 |pages=8-9 |publisher=Committee for Skeptical Inquiry}}</ref> 
